      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De bonitate</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e104">Gregorius, <title>super Ezechielem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e112">Omne bonum, quod agimus, per intentionem semper
              ad coelestia levemus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e119">Gregorius, <title>super Ezechielem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e127">Hi veraciter boni sunt, qui in bonitate
              persistere etiam inter malos possunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e142">Quantum vos in bono profecistis, tantum bona
              etiam de alienis sentitis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e157">Bona Deo accepta non sunt, quae ante oculos ejus
              malorum admixtione maculantur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e165">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e173">Bona quae hominibus innotescunt, sine periculo
              vix esse possunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e180">Gregorius, in <title>Dialogis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e188">Multa videntur bona, sed non sunt, quia bono
              animo non fiunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e195">Gregorius, in <title>Dialogis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e203">Vitae vera aestimatio in virtute est operum, non
              in ostensione signorum. Nam sunt plerique, qui et signa non faciunt, signa tamen
              facientibus dispares non sunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e210">Gregorius, <title>super Ezechielem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e218">Bonum valde est quod justus tribuit, quando male
              agentibus libera voce contradicit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e223">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e233" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e225">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e233">Bonarum mentium est, et ibi aliquo modo culpas
              suas agnoscere, ubi culpa non est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e238">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e248" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e240">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e248">Vestrum sine dubio bonum facitis, si bona
              volentibus opem fertis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e254">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e264" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e256">Augustinus, <title>de Verbis Domini</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e264">Potes aurum perdere et nolens, potes domum,
              potes honores, potes ipsam casu salutem; bonum vero, quo vere bonus es, nec invitus
              accipis, nec invitus amittis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e269">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e279" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e271">Augustinus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e279">Quis est in hac vita sine aliquo peccato? Sed
              eum dicimus bonum, cujus praevalent bona; illumque optimum, qui peccat
              minimum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e284">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e294" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e286">Augustinus, <title>de Natura boni</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e294">Et omne bonum a Deo est: omnis ergo natura a Deo
              est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e299">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e309" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e301">Augustinus, <title>de Natura boni</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e309">Omnia quanto magis moderata, speciosa, ordinata
              sunt, tanto magis bona sunt; quanto autem minus moderata, minus speciosa, minus
              ordinata sunt, minus bona sunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e314">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e324" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e316">Augustinus, <title>de Virginitate</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e324">Aliquando alter fructuosus est donis
              paucioribus, sed potioribus; alter inferioribus, sed pluribus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e329">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e339" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e331">Augustinus, <title>de Libero arbitrio</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e339">Bonum est aliquid homo: et melius quam pecus, ex
              eo quod praecepti capax: et hoc melius, cum praeceptum jam cepit: rursum hoc melius,
              cum praecepto paruit: et his omnibus melius, cum aeternae lumine sapientiae beatus
              est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e345">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e355" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e347">Joannes Chrysostomus, <title>de Militia
              Christiana</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e355">Non agamus similem infidelibus vitam; sed a
              quibus fide discernimur, ab eorum studiis, etiam et moribus dividamur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e360">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e370" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e362">Joannes Chrysostomus, in <title>Sermonibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e370">Pietati hoc proprium est, ut in tenebris
              fulgeat; impietas autem, etsi in lumine fuerit, tenebrescit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e375">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e385" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e377">Bernardus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e385">Minime pro certo est bonus, qui melior esse non
              vult; et ubi incipis nolle fieri melior, ibi desinis etiam esse bonus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e390">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e400" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e392">Bernardus, <title>super Cantica</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e400">Non mediocris titulus profecto virtutis, inter
              pravos vivere bonum, et inter malignantes innocentiae retinere candorem et morum
              lenitatem.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e405">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e415" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e407">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e415">Tranquillitas animi, et expulsis erroribus
              absoluta libertas, quaeris quae sit ista? Non homines timere; non turpia velle, nec
              nimia; in seipsum maximam habere potestatem: inaestimabile bonum est suum
              fleri.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e420">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e430" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e422">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e430">Nulla sine Deo mens bona est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e436">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e446" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e438">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e446">Pars magna bonitatis est velle fieri
              bonum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-d1e451">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e461" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Rd1e453">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e42380-Qd1e461">Animus nunquam major est, quam ubi aliena
              seposuit, et fecit sibi pacem nihil timendo, fecit sibi divitias nihil
              concupiscendo.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
